<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - ROCKWELL 9, 10, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - REMOVE -
        REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put a pry bar between the case and the end of the idler shaft to keep the lower reverse
                idler shaft from moving. Remove the nut and washer that fastens the gear on the shaft
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303370">(Figure 70</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the reverse idler gear, the two spacer washers, the bearing race and the needle
                bearing assembly while removing the shaft
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303371">(Figure 71</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1303370" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303370.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 70. Remove Nut and Washer</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1303371" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303371.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Figure 71. Remove Reverse Idler Gear, Spacer Washer, Bearing Race and Needle Bearing Assembly
            </caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
